<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>No. 1338
                    The Deputy Director of the Office of Near Eastern and African
                        Affairs (
                        Allen
                    ) to the Director of Near Eastern and African
                        Affairs (
                        Henderson
                    )Sent to the Acting Secretary of State
                        over the signature of Byrnes.</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945Berlinv02</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d1338</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">1338</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-07-18T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-07-18T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="1338" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1338">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Potsdam/7–1845: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1338<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Deputy Director of the Office of Near Eastern and African
                        Affairs</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_AD2" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Allen</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Director of Near Eastern and African
                        Affairs</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HLW1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Henderson</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d1338fn1">Sent to the Acting Secretary of State
                        over the signature of <persName corresp="#p_BJF1">Byrnes</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Babelsberg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-18">July 18,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Victory1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Victory</hi>
                    </gloss> 82. To Acting Secretary of State for <persName corresp="#p_HLW1">Loy
                        Henderson</persName> from <persName corresp="#p_AGV1">George
                        Allen</persName>.</p>
                <p>Sent to Department. Repeated to Paris and Tangier for <persName corresp="#p_VHS1">Villard</persName> and Ailing.</p>
                <p>Russians have proposed addition of Tangier and the Levant states to the agenda
                    for the conference.<note n="2" xml:id="d1338fn2">See <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_46">pp. 46</ref>, <ref target="#pg_55">55</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>There is, as yet, no indication of Russian attitude regarding either
                    question.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
